						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> infront of the rock-cut cave.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 5: 976 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The letters of this inscription are clumsily engraved. It states that the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the temple of Paramēśvara at Pūvālaikkuḍi was built by the temple official, Vāduḷi Ūraṉ Tuṟṟiṉṉai.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 123. </p>						

